Concordia (Townsfolk): Five players start with resources. Each night, they may pass a resource to another player. If you have all resources, learn the Demon.
Resources: brick, food, tool, wine, cloth
Coup (Townsfolk): Two players start with Contessas. Each night, each player with a Contessa chooses a player to pass the Contessa to.
One Night Ultimate Werewolf (Townsfolk): Once per game, at night, choose a player: you swap roles and alignments.
Potion Explosion (Townsfolk): Each night, choose a player: learn if their neighbors are the same character class.
Resistance (Townsfolk): Each night, choose 4 players: you learn if all are Townsfolk.
Munchkin (Outsider): You think you are a Townsfolk character, but you are not. You receive arbitrary Amnesiac question answers unless you Bingo.
Wavelength (Outsider): Each night, choose 2 players (not yourself): they are asked a question. If they answer differently, they are drunk until dusk.
Lords of Waterdeep (Minion): Each night, choose a player and a statement: they are “mad” about this statement tomorrow, or might be executed.
Coup (Demon): Each night*, choose a player: they die. Or, choose 2 players: they die if they do not have a Contessa.

Bluffs:
Exit (Townsfolk): Each night, choose a player: you receive a hint about their ability.
Quacks of Quedlinburg (Townsfolk): Each night*, you may choose a player: if they are not a Townsfolk, you die. You may repeat this ability.
Arkham Horror (Outsider): Each night, choose a player: something bad might happen to them.
